1 INTRODUCTION
Air travel is a task that millions of people perform regularly, yet the digital tools designed to support it often create unnecessary friction at the most critical mo- ments. The boarding pass which was once a simple paper ticket has migrated to mobile apps, but its design has not kept pace with the opportunity mobile inter- faces provide. Instead of adapting to the traveler’s context, most airline mobile boarding passes present a dense, undifferentiated wall of information: confir- mation number, frequent flyer number, seat assignment, gate number, boarding time, departure time, flight number, TSA PreCheck status, baggage claim details, and more.
This project focuses on the task of navigating an airport using a mobile boarding pass, from the moment a traveler arrives at security through gate boarding and finally reaching their seat. What users are trying to accomplish is not a single task but a sequence of micro-tasks, each requiring a different and specific subset of information. At the security checkpoint, a traveler needs their name and barcode. At the gate, they need their gate number, boarding time, and boarding group. At their seat, they need their seat number. The mismatch between what the interface displays and what the user needs at any given moment imposes unnecessary cognitive load and creates a frustrating, error-prone experience.
The motivation for this project emerged from personal observation and a widely shared pain point among frequent and occasional flyers alike. Standing in a security line, phone brightness turned up, scanning through a cluttered screen searching for the barcode while a TSA agent waits, is a stressful and common experience. A passenger in the wrong boarding group who cannot quickly locate their group number holds up an entire boarding queue.
The goal of this project is to explore, prototype, and evaluate a redesigned air- line mobile boarding pass that surfaces the right information at the right time, reducing cognitive load and supporting travelers through each distinct stage of their airport journey.
