Synthesize 3 distinct design alternatives I could prototype, each with a genuinely different interaction paradigm. Include how boarding time countdown is han- dled in each.
CLAUDE (AI)
Three distinct alternatives:
Alternative 1 — Stage Spotlight (Automated Progressive Disclosure): The board- ing pass opens to a focus panel that automatically surfaces the most critical information for the current stage — QR code at security, boarding time + de- pleting arc + zone at the gate, seat number after boarding. All other details are always one tap away in a collapsed drawer. The paradigm is the interface comes to the traveler.
Alternative 2 — Three-Card Pass (Explicit User-Controlled Navigation): Three la- beled swipeable cards — Security, Gate, Boarding — each with a single dominant hero field and strict hierarchy. The Gate card shows zone in 72pt as the hero, boarding time with a slim countdown bar as the supporting field. The active card is auto-selected by time but the traveler retains full manual control via tabs; nothing is ever hidden. The paradigm is you are always in control, but the right default is already selected.
Alternative 3 — Ambient Pass (Lock Screen + Widget Presence): The boarding pass lives as a home screen widget and lock screen Live Activity, surfacing one field at a time without opening the app. At the gate: gate number + boarding time + slim countdown bar in a compact chip on the lock screen. After boarding: seat number in large type. Full pass accessible via one tap. The paradigm is the information finds the traveler.
